<html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/tips.css"></head><body><p><b>Logging breakpoints</b></p><p>If you want to log program state during debugging, use non-suspending breakpoints. Select the expression that you want to log, hold <span class="shortcut">Shift</span>, and click the gutter at the line where the expression should be logged.</p><p>In the example, <span class="code_emphasis">sent.size()</span> will be logged upon reaching line 24.</p><p class="image"><img src="images/ij_tips_log_breakpoint.png" alt="Non-suspending breakpoint" style="border: 1px solid #55555;" /></p></body></html>